The paper deals with parameterized complexity and graph algorithms, which are typically covered in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. The specific problems studied in the paper, such as Minimum Fill-In and Interval Completion, are related to chordal graphs, which fall under the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The use of Probabilistically Checkable Proofs (PCPs) also suggests a connection to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. Finally, the mention of Feedback Arc Set in Tournaments indicates a possible connection to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
